Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek black-figured pottery vessel, probably krater or dinos; interior reserved; exterior: white slip; part of three naked male dancers to right: preserved: on left, part of foot, raised left leg and finger tip; most of middle figure (head lost; incised anatomical details); on right, right arm of another figure. Below, glazed area with some seemingly ancient vertical incisions.
Curator's comments: From the same vase as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum 6535.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.8)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1051)
